==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stannel
<hw>Stan"nel</hw> <pr>(-n⟦ecr⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>st⟦amac⟧ngella</ets>, <ets>stangilla</ets>; properly, stone yeller,
<it>i. e.</it>, a bird that yells from the rocks. See <er>Stone</er>,
and <er>Yell</er>, and cf. <er>Stonegall</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The kestrel; -- called also <altname>standgale</altname>,
<altname>standgall</altname>, <altname>stanchel</altname>,
<altname>stand hawk</altname>, <altname>stannel hawk</altname>,
<altname>steingale</altname>, <altname>stonegall</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>staniel</asp>, <asp>stannyel</asp>, and
<asp>stanyel</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With what wing the <qex>staniel</qex> checks at it.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stannic</ent>⟦br⟧
